title: Grateful Dead Live at Winterland Arena on 1977-03-19
description:
Set 1

Bertha, Mama Tried, Loser, Big River, They Love Each Other, Looks Like Rain, Tennessee Jed, Estimated Prophet, Terrapin Station-> Playin' In The Band-> Samson & Delilah-> Playin' In The Band

Set 2

Eyes Of The World-> Dancin' In The Streets-> Wharf Rat-> Franklin's Tower-> Sugar Magnolia, E: One More Saturday Night, E: Uncle John's Band*

*Second Encore

reviews.review_text:
Beautiful Matrix. And A Foreshadow Of The Year To Come. What's really impressive about this offering is the board and the mix. It's just exactly perfect. The SBD is warm and fuzzy, everybody's relaxed, and everything is well balanced. I usually have to do a smidgeon of tweaking with reverb and/or bass and/or treble to get things right. Not tonight! I didn't have to touch a thing. Hunter did a superb job on this show.  Of course, it helps tremendously when you have a beautiful soundboard to work with.  It reminds me of Betty's work.

One of the things I love about tonight is the interesting lineup of both sets.  The Boyz continue the uniqueness they showed throughout 1976.  I mean Estimated, Terrapin > PITB > Samson > PITB in the first set?  Really!?  And though the second is a bit short, I've never seen another one like it.

Highly recommended - especially for those who don't have editing equipment. Bravo Hunter! The standard matrix maker of the industry.

Best of '77 To me, this is THE show of year. Hunter's mix here is a big upgrade from the other matrix that has been available. There is oodles of home-field warmth in this particular show and the band is locked in from the get-go. Musically, this show is fantastic and, to me, easily surpasses anything they did during the subsequent much-vaunted May tour. A boast? Listen for yourselves. Garcia's tone with his new envelope filter is spectacular; be sure to check out the potpourri of dazzling sounds that Garcia uses in the Playing In The Band sandwich.
A real thought jewel polisher..ty,Hunter My god...you saved me again Hunter...ty
